---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import CtaSection from '../../components/CtaSection.astro';
---
<Base title="Healthcare Software Delivery" description="Predictable software delivery for healthcare companies. HIPAA compliance, clinical workflows, and patient safety — delivered on forecast." fullWidth>

  <div class="hero-dark hero-centered">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Healthcare</span>
      <h1>HIPAA-compliant delivery<br><em>from day one</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-subtext">Patient-facing software doesn't get a second chance. Compliance can't be retrofitted. Your delivery partner needs to build it right the first time — and ship it on schedule.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ind-challenges">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-heading">The problem with healthcare software</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Healthcare technology operates under constraints that most development teams treat as afterthoughts.</p>

      <div class="steps-grid">
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>HIPAA Compliance</h3>
          <p>HIPAA isn't a checkbox at the end of a build. It's an architectural constraint that shapes every data model, every API, every deployment decision. Retrofitting compliance into a shipped product is expensive and dangerous.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>Clinical Workflows</h3>
          <p>Clinical software integrates with EHR systems, lab platforms, and provider networks. Every integration point is a dependency that affects your timeline — and most dev teams don't account for that until it's too late.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>Patient Safety</h3>
          <p>When software touches patient care, bugs aren't just inconveniences — they're risks. Every delivery needs to be validated against clinical requirements, not just acceptance criteria written by product managers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>Regulatory Deadlines</h3>
          <p>FDA submissions, state health department requirements, payer certification windows — these deadlines are set by agencies, not product teams. Your development timeline either aligns with them or you miss the window.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ind-solution">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Predictive Delivery</span>
      <h2>How we solve it</h2>
      <p>Predictive delivery gives healthcare teams the confidence that compliance, clinical requirements, and regulatory deadlines are built into the plan — not discovered along the way.</p>
      <ul class="ind-solution-list">
        <li><strong>Compliance from the first delivery.</strong> HIPAA requirements are baked into our delivery architecture from day one. Data handling, access controls, audit logging, and encryption are not late-stage additions.</li>
        <li><strong>Forecasted against your regulatory calendar.</strong> NolteOS maps your delivery timeline against real deadlines. You'll know weeks in advance whether a submission window is at risk — not the day before.</li>
        <li><strong>Clinical validation built into acceptance.</strong> Every delivery includes acceptance criteria that account for clinical workflow requirements, not just functional specifications.</li>
        <li><strong>Transparent, auditable progress.</strong> Real-time delivery metrics provide the documentation trail that compliance teams and auditors need — automatically, not as a manual exercise.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="case-studies">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Proven in production</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Real healthcare software, delivered predictably.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="case-grid ind-case-single">
      <div class="case-card">
        <div class="case-card-top">
          <span class="case-card-logo-text">Breeze</span>
          <div class="case-card-metrics">
            <span class="case-metric">47 <span class="case-metric-label">deliveries</span></span>
            <span class="case-metric">100% <span class="case-metric-label">accuracy</span></span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="case-card-body">
          <div class="case-card-meta-line">
            <span class="case-pill">Healthcare</span>
            <span class="case-stage">Series A</span>
          </div>
          <h3>Breeze Oral Care</h3>
          <p class="case-desc">HIPAA-compliant dental platform built from discovery to launch in four months. On time, on budget, to the dollar.</p>
          <div class="case-meta">
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">2 years</span><span class="case-meta-label">Partnership</span></div>
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">47</span><span class="case-meta-label">Deliveries</span></div>
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">100%</span><span class="case-meta-label">Accuracy</span></div>
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">HIPAA</span><span class="case-meta-label">Compliance</span></div>
          </div>
          <a class="case-link" href="/work/breeze-oral-care">Read the full case study &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CtaSection />

</Base>

<style>
  .ind-challenges {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--white);
  }
  .ind-solution {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--gray-100);
  }
  .ind-solution h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .ind-solution p {
    max-width: 640px;
    color: var(--gray-600);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .ind-solution-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 2rem 0 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 640px;
  }
  .ind-solution-list li {
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--gray-600);
  }
  .ind-solution-list strong {
    color: var(--black);
  }
  .ind-case-single {
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .case-studies {
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }
</style>
